definition: The test code representing each subject characteristic.
term: CDISC SDTM Subject Characteristic Test Code Terminology

name: Subject Characteristic Test Name
definition: The test name representing each subject characteristic.
term: CDISC SDTM Subject Characteristic Test Name Terminology

name: Sudden Death Syndrome Type
definition: A terminology codelist that describes syndromes or conditions that put a subject at risk for sudden death.
term: CDISC SDTM Sudden Death Syndrome Type Terminology

name: Supporting Evidence for Re-Treatment
definition: Terminology relevant to the clinical evidence to support reason for re-treatment of disease.
term: CDISC SDTM Supporting Evidence for Re-Treatment Terminology

name: TIMI Flow Responses
definition: A terminology codelist of acceptable values to describe TIMI Flow.
term: CDISC SDTM Thrombolysis in Myocardial Infarction Flow Responses Terminology

name: Treatment Episode
definition: Terminology relevant to whether an individual is being treated for a disease for the first time.
term: CDISC SDTM Treatment Episode Terminology

name: Treatment Failure Reason
definition: Terminology relevant to the reason the drug or therapy was unsuccessful in treating the condition.
term: CDISC SDTM Treatment Failure Reason Terminology

name: Trial Blinding Schema
definition: The name of a code list that contains terms to define the type of blinding for the trial. (NCI)
term: CDISC SDTM Trial Blinding Schema Terminology

name: Trial Indication Type
definition: The name of a code list that contains terms to define the type of trial, e.g. cure or prevention. (NCI)
term: CDISC SDTM Trial Indication Type Terminology

name: Trial Phase
definition: Clinical trials are broken into three or four phases: Phase I tests a new drug or treatment for safety in a small group; Phase II expands the study to a larger group of people; Phase III expands the study to an even larger group of people to measure whether the treatment actually benefits patients, and whether its benefits exceed its risks; and Phase IV takes place after the drug or treatment has been licensed and marketed. (NCI)
term: CDISC SDTM Trial Phase Terminology

name: Trial Summary Parameter Test Code
definition: The test code for an individual characteristic of a clinical trial, e.g. description of trial design, trial blinding schema, and primary objective of trial.
term: CDISC SDTM Trial Summary Parameter Terminology by Code

name: Trial Summary Parameter Test Name
definition: The test name for an individual characteristic of a clinical trial, e.g. description of trial design, trial blinding schema, and primary objective of trial.
term: CDISC SDTM Trial Summary Parameter Terminology by Name

name: Trial Type
definition: The type of clinical trial performed e.g. efficacy, safety. (NCI)
term: CDISC SDTM Trial Type Terminology

name: Tumor Identification Test Code
definition: Terminology relevant to the test codes that describe tumor assessments for identification purposes.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor Identification Test Code Terminology

name: Tumor Identification Test Name
definition: Terminology relevant to the test names that describe tumor assessments for identification purposes.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor Identification Test Name Terminology

name: Tumor Response Assessment Test Code
definition: Terminology relevant to the test codes that describe an assessment of tumor response to treatment or therapy.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor Response Assessment Test Code Terminology

name: Tumor Response Assessment Test Name
definition: Terminology relevant to the test names that describe an assessment of tumor response to treatment or therapy.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor Response Assessment Test Name Terminology

name: Tumor Response Result
definition: The result of an assessment of tumor response to treatment or therapy.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor Response Result Terminology

name: Tumor and Lesion Identification Results
definition: Terminology relevant to tumor and lesion identification results.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor and Lesion Identification Result Terminology

name: Tumor or Lesion Properties Test Code
synonym: Tumor or Lesion Properties Test Code
definition: Terminology relevant to the test codes that describe the assessment or measurement of a tumor, lesion or site of disease.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor or Lesion Properties Test Code Terminology

name: Tumor or Lesion Properties Test Name
synonym: Tumor or Lesion Properties Test Name
definition: Terminology relevant to the test codes that describe the assessment or measurement of a tumor, lesion or site of disease.
term: CDISC SDTM Tumor or Lesion Properties Test Name Terminology

name: Unit
definition: Terminology codelist used for units within CDISC.
term: CDISC SDTM Unit of Measure Terminology

name: Units for Vital Signs Results
definition: The unit used to record and describe the result of a test investigating a vital sign. (NCI)
term: CDISC SDTM Unit for Vital Sign Result Terminology

name: Vaccination Evidence Source
definition: Terminology relevant to the source of information regarding the subject's vaccination status.
term: CDISC SDTM Vaccination Evidence Source Terminology

name: Viral Resistance Findings Test Code
definition: Terminology used for virology test codes of the CDISC Study Data Tabulation Model.
term: CDISC SDTM Viral Resistance Findings Test Code Terminology

name: Viral Resistance Findings Test Name
definition: Terminology used for virology test names of the CDISC Study Data Tabulation Model.
term: CDISC SDTM Viral Resistance Findings Test Name Terminology

name: Vital Signs Test Code
definition: The test code given to the test that analyzes a particular set of vital signs including temperature, respiratory rate, heart rate, and blood pressure.
term: CDISC SDTM Vital Sign Terminology by Code

name: Vital Signs Test Name
definition: The test name given to the test that analyzes a particular set of vital signs including temperature, respiratory rate, heart rate, and blood pressure.
term: CDISC SDTM Vital Sign Terminology by Name

name: West Haven Hepatic Encephalopathy Grade
definition: A grading system to describe the severity of hepatic encephalopathy based on the level of mental status by the West Haven Hepatic Encephalopathy Grade.
term: CDISC SDTM West Haven Hepatic Encephalopathy Grade Terminology
